text:
Very disappointing for a 4 star hotel:
- I felt cramped from the first moment I stepped in, the lobby is small, and the rooms the smallest I've ever seen in any U.S. hotel;
- The room was basic, and another first was that there was no mini-fridge in the room where you could keep some cool water;
- There was a patch of paint on the ceiling that was scraped / stripped;
These are all minor details, but I've seen better at any 3 star hotel I've stayed at.

The 2 star review is because of the following, which I don't expect from any respectable establishment: 
There was no heating in the entire building following several cold days (mid september). I had a hard time falling asleep due to the cold. Some friends stopped by to take some luggage and they complained as well, even though they were dressed for outdoors. When I asked at the reception, all I got was that the heating is turned off in the entire building, so it's best I stop the fan as it's only making things worse. Unbelievable.
